[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-Sun May  3 09:30:05 UTC 2015 - astieger@suse.com
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-- GNU awk 4.1.2:
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  * manual improved
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  * The debugger's "restart" command now works again.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  * Redirected getline is now allowed inside BEGINFILE/ENDFILE.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  * A number of bugs have been fixed in the MPFR code.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  * Indirect function calls now work for both built-in and extension
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-    functions.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  * Built-in functions are now included in FUNCTAB.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  * In non-English locales, it was accidentally possible to use
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-    non-english letters for identifiers
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  * The "where" command has been added to the debugger as an alias
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-    for "backtrace".
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  * Gawk no longer explicitly checks the current directory after
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-    doing a path search of AWKPATH.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  * Infrastructure upgrades: Automake 1.15, Gettext 0.19.4,
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-    Libtool 2.4.6, Bison 3.0.4.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  * If a user-defined function has a parameter with the same name
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-    as another user-defined function, it is no longer possible to
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-    call the second function from inside the first.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  * POSIX requires that the names of function parameters not be the
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-    same as any of the special built-in variables and also not
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-    conflict with the names of any functions. Gawk has checked for
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-    the former since 3.1.7. With --posix, it now also checks for
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-    the latter.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  * The test suite should check for necessary locales and skip the
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-    tests where it matters if support isn't what it should be.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  * Gawk now expects to be compiled on a system with multibyte
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-    character support.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-- drop gawk-4.1.1-build-baddest.patch, upstream
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-
