[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-- GNU awk 4.1.1:
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  * The "stat" extension now includes a "devbsize" element which
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-    indicates the units for the "nblocks" element.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  * A number of bugs in the pretty-printing / profiling code have
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-    been fixed.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  * The -O option now works again.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  * The --include option, documented since 4.0, now actually works.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  * Infrastructure updated to automake 1.13.4, bison 3.0.2, and
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-    libtool 2.4.2.418.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  * The configure script now accepts a --disable-extensions option,
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-    which disables checking for and building the extensions.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  * The API now provides functions pointers for malloc(), calloc(),
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-    realloc() and free(), to insure that the same memory allocation
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-    functions are always used. This bumps the minor version by one.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  * The printf quote flag now works correctly in locales with
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-    a different decimal point character but without a thousands
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-    separator character. If the thousands separator is a string,
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-    it will be correctly added to decimal numbers.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  * The readfile extension now has an input parser that will read
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-    whole files as a single record.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-- packaging changes:
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  * remove added German po file and scanning of translations
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  * remove profiling, fixing warning make-check-outside-check-section
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  * remove autoreconf call
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  * drop gawk-3.1.8.diff 
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  * drop older-automake.diff, not required for factory
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  * build with libsigsegv
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  * no not regenerate info pages
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  * add gawk-4.1.1-build-baddest.patch required for install
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  * switch to xz tarball
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  * verify source signature
