[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-Mon May 13 09:35:02 UTC 2013 - idonmez@suse.com
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-- Update to version 4.1.0
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  * The three executables gawk, pgawk, and dgawk, have been merged into
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-    one, named just gawk.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  * The new -i option (from xgawk) is used for loading awk library files.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  * The new -l option (from xgawk) is used for loading dynamic extensions.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  * The dynamic extension interface has been completely redone.  There is
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-    now a defined API for C extensions to use.  A C extension acts like
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-    a function written in awk, except that it cannot do everything that awk
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-    code can. However, this allows interfacing to any facility that is
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-    available from C.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  * The "inplace" extension, built using the new facility, can be used to
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-    simulate the GNU "sed -i" feature.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  * The and(), or() and xor() functions now take any number of arguments,
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-    with a minimum of two.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  * New arrays: SYMTAB, FUNCTAB, and PROCINFO["identifiers"]. SYMTAB allows
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-    indirect access to any defined variable or array; it is possible to
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-    "walk" the symbol table, if that should be necessary.
