[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-Mon Nov 12 14:50:34 CET 2007 - schwab@suse.de
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-- Update to gawk 3.1.6.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  1. `gawk 'program' /non/existant/file' no longer core dumps.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  2. Too many people the world over have complained about gawk's use of the
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-     locale's decimal point for parsing input data instead of the traditional
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-     period.  So, even though gawk was being nicely standards-compliant, in
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-     a Triumph For The Users, gawk now only uses the locale's decimal point
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-     if --posix is supplied or if POSIXLY_CORRECT is set.  It is the sincere
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-     hope that this change will eliminate this FAQ from being asked.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  3. `gawk -v BINMODE=1 ...' works again.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  4. Internal file names like `/dev/user' now work again. (Note that these
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-     file names are obsolete and will go away eventually.)
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  5. Problems with wide strings in non "C" locales have been straightened
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-     out everywhere.  (At least, we think so.)
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  6. Use of `ansi2knr' is no longer supported. Please use an ANSI C compiler.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  7. Updated to Autoconf 2.61, Automake 1.10, and Gettext 0.16.1.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  8. The getopt* and regex* files were synchronized with current GLIBC CVS.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-     See the ChangeLog for the versions and minor edits made.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  9. There are additional --lint-old warnings.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  10. Gawk now uses getaddrinfo(3) to look up names and IP addresses. This
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-      allows the use of an IPv6 format address and paves the way for
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-      eventual addition of `/inet6/...' and `/inet4/...' hostnames.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  11. We believe gawk to now be valgrind clean. At least when run against
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-      the test suite.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  12. A number of issues dealing with the formatting and printing of very
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-      large numbers in integer formats have been dealt with and fixed.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  13. Gawk now converts "+inf", "-inf", "+nan" and "-nan" into the corresponding
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-      magic IEEE floating point values. Only those strings (case independent)
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-      work.  With --posix, gawk calls the system strtod directly. You asked
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-      for it, you got it, you deal with it.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  14. Defining YYDEBUG enables the -D command line option.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  15. Gawk should now work out of the box on Tandem NSK/OSS systems.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  16. Lint messages rationalized: many more of the messages are now printed
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-      only once, instead of every time they are encountered.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  17. The strftime() function now accepts an optional third argument, which
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-      if non-zero or non-null, indicates that the time should be formatted
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-      as UTC instead of as local time.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  18. The precedence of concatenation and `| getline' (in something like
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-      "echo " "date" | getline stuff) has been reverted to the earlier
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-      behavior and now once again matches Unix awk.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  19. New configure time flag --disable-directories-fatal which causes
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-      gawk to silently skip directories on the command line.  This behavior
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-      is also enabled for --traditional, since it's what Unix awk does.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  20. A new option, --use-lc-numeric, forces use of the locale's decimal
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-      point without the rest of the draconian restrictions imposed by
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-      --posix. This softens somewhat the stance taken in item #2.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  21. Everything relevant has been updated to the GPL 3.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  22. Array growth should be faster now, at no cost in space.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  23. Lots more tests.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  24. One new translation.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-  25. Various bugs fixed, see the ChangeLog for details.
[0m[31m[TOOL][0m [31m-
